originalText.text: Sadly, the customer service is HORRENDOUS. Lisa (presumed the owner-which is even more incredible if this is the case) emails were very short & flippant. When I emailed for the tracking number info so i may see where the delivery was in progress (which i was told would be supplied once basket was shipped) The person emailed me back with just a tracking number (no Carrier) when i emailed again asking for the carrier the person named Lisa email ‘UPS’…just like that. Maybe if her general tone in previous emails were friendlier it wouldn’t have come across so rude. As a small business owner I INTENTIONALLY seek out local small businesses to support. The experience i had was so disappointing and when I mentioned in f/u email that my experience wasn’t the best, the person named Lisa emails me a LONG drafted email of all the things she did right! Like all the effort needed to draft the long email, she could have put that same effort in service recovery. I block her emails now in hopes to end the back and forth with her. Do better.
